def show_image_pair(degraded, clean, title="", figsize=(10, 4)):
    """     """
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=figsize)
    
    # Tensor -> numpy 
    if isinstance(degraded, torch.Tensor):
        degraded = degraded.permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
        degraded = (degraded * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)  # [-1,1] -> [0,1]
    if isinstance(clean, torch.Tensor):
        clean = clean.permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
        clean = (clean * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
    
    axes[0].imshow(degraded)
    axes[0].set_title('Degraded')
    axes[0].axis('off')
    
    axes[1].imshow(clean)
    axes[1].set_title('Clean (GT)')
    axes[1].axis('off')
    
    if title:
        fig.suptitle(title, fontsize=12)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def show_sample_grid(dataset, n_samples=4, title=""):
    """    """
    if len(dataset) == 0:
        print(f" : {title}")
        return
    
    n_samples = min(n_samples, len(dataset))
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, n_samples, figsize=(3*n_samples, 6))
    
    indices = np.random.choice(len(dataset), n_samples, replace=False)
    
    for i, idx in enumerate(indices):
        item = dataset[idx]
        degraded = item['degraded']
        clean = item['clean']
        
        # Tensor -> numpy
        if isinstance(degraded, torch.Tensor):
            degraded = degraded.permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
            degraded = (degraded * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
        if isinstance(clean, torch.Tensor):
            clean = clean.permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
            clean = (clean * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
        
        axes[0, i].imshow(degraded)
        axes[0, i].axis('off')
        if i == 0:
            axes[0, i].set_ylabel('Degraded', fontsize=10)
        
        axes[1, i].imshow(clean)
        axes[1, i].axis('off')
        if i == 0:
            axes[1, i].set_ylabel('Clean', fontsize=10)
    
    if title:
        fig.suptitle(title, fontsize=14)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def dataset_statistics(dataset, name=""):
    """  """
    print(f"\n{'='*50}")
    print(f" {name}  ")
    print(f"{'='*50}")
    print(f"    : {len(dataset)}")
    
    if len(dataset) > 0:
        sample = dataset[0]
        print(f"   : {sample['degraded'].shape}")
        print(f"   : {sample['degraded'].dtype}")
        print(f"   : [{sample['degraded'].min():.2f}, {sample['degraded'].max():.2f}]")

3. ImageNet-C

corruption

Corruption Categories (glass_blur, fog ):

  • Noise: gaussian_noise, shot_noise, impulse_noise
  • Blur: defocus_blur, motion_blur, zoom_blur
  • Weather: snow, frost, brightness
  • Digital: contrast, elastic_transform, pixelate, jpeg_compression

:

  • Corrupted: Corrupted_new/{corruption}/{severity}/*.JPEG
  • Clean: GT/*.JPEG
In[4]:
if PATHS['imagenet'].exists():
    # Tiny-ImageNet-C 64x64 
    transform = get_default_transform(image_size=64, train=False)
    
    # Corruption category  
    corruption_categories = ['noise', 'blur', 'weather', 'digital']
    
    print("=" * 60)
    print("ImageNet-C Corruption Categories")
    print("=" * 60)
    
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(corruption_categories), 4, figsize=(16, 4*len(corruption_categories)))
    
    for row, category in enumerate(corruption_categories):
        try:
            dataset = ImageNetCDataset(
                root=str(PATHS['imagenet']),
                corruption_category=category,
                severity=3,
                transform=transform
            )
            
            print(f"\n[{category.upper()}] {len(dataset)} samples")
            
            # 2   ( degraded, clean)
            for col in range(2):
                if len(dataset) > col:
                    idx = np.random.randint(len(dataset))
                    item = dataset[idx]
                    
                    degraded = item['degraded'].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
                    degraded = (degraded * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
                    clean = item['clean'].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
                    clean = (clean * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
                    
                    axes[row, col*2].imshow(degraded)
                    axes[row, col*2].set_title(f'{category.upper()} - Corrupted')
                    axes[row, col*2].axis('off')
                    
                    axes[row, col*2+1].imshow(clean)
                    axes[row, col*2+1].set_title(f'{category.upper()} - Clean')
                    axes[row, col*2+1].axis('off')
                    
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"[{category}] Error: {e}")
            for col in range(4):
                axes[row, col].text(0.5, 0.5, f'Error: {category}', ha='center', va='center')
                axes[row, col].axis('off')
    
    plt.suptitle('ImageNet-C: Corrupted vs Clean Comparison', fontsize=14, y=1.02)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
else:
    print("ImageNet-C  .")

In[5]:
#   : Corrupted vs Clean + Difference Map
if PATHS['imagenet'].exists():
    transform = get_default_transform(image_size=64, train=False)
    
    # noise  
    dataset = ImageNetCDataset(
        root=str(PATHS['imagenet']),
        corruption_category='noise',
        severity=3,
        transform=transform
    )
    
    if len(dataset) > 0:
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 4, figsize=(16, 8))
        
        for row in range(2):
            idx = np.random.randint(len(dataset))
            item = dataset[idx]
            
            degraded = item['degraded'].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
            degraded = (degraded * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
            clean = item['clean'].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
            clean = (clean * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
            
            # Difference map ()
            diff = np.abs(degraded - clean)
            diff_amplified = (diff * 5).clip(0, 1)  #  
            
            axes[row, 0].imshow(degraded)
            axes[row, 0].set_title('Corrupted (Noise)')
            axes[row, 0].axis('off')
            
            axes[row, 1].imshow(clean)
            axes[row, 1].set_title('Clean (GT)')
            axes[row, 1].axis('off')
            
            axes[row, 2].imshow(diff)
            axes[row, 2].set_title('Difference |C-D|')
            axes[row, 2].axis('off')
            
            axes[row, 3].imshow(diff_amplified)
            axes[row, 3].set_title('Difference (5x amplified)')
            axes[row, 3].axis('off')
        
        plt.suptitle('Corrupted vs Clean: Difference Analysis', fontsize=14)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
        
        #  
        print(f"\nDifference Statistics:")
        print(f"  Mean diff: {diff.mean():.4f}")
        print(f"  Max diff:  {diff.max():.4f}")
        print(f"  Degraded != Clean: {not np.allclose(degraded, clean)}")

Difference Statistics:
  Mean diff: 0.0985
  Max diff:  0.4471
  Degraded != Clean: True

#   
datasets = {}

# ImageNet-C (64x64)
if PATHS['imagenet'].exists():
    transform_64 = get_default_transform(image_size=64, train=False)
    ds = ImageNetCDataset(
        root=str(PATHS['imagenet']),
        corruption_category='noise',  # noise  
        severity=3,
        transform=transform_64
    )
    if len(ds) > 0:
        datasets['imagenet-noise'] = ds
        print(f"imagenet-noise: {len(ds)} samples")

#   (256x256   )
transform_256 = get_default_transform(image_size=256, train=False)

for name in ['ldct', 'dibco', 'fmd']:
    path = PATHS[name]
    if path.exists():
        split = 'test' if name == 'ldct' else 'train'
        try:
            ds = get_dataset(name, str(path), split=split, transform=transform_256)
            if len(ds) > 0:
                datasets[name] = ds
                print(f"{name}: {len(ds)} samples")
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"{name}: Error - {e}")

if datasets:
    n_domains = len(datasets)
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, n_domains, figsize=(4*n_domains, 8))
    
    if n_domains == 1:
        axes = axes.reshape(2, 1)
    
    for i, (name, ds) in enumerate(datasets.items()):
        idx = np.random.randint(len(ds))
        item = ds[idx]
        
        degraded = item['degraded'].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
        degraded = (degraded * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
        clean = item['clean'].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()
        clean = (clean * 0.5 + 0.5).clip(0, 1)
        
        axes[0, i].imshow(degraded)
        axes[0, i].set_title(f'{name.upper()}\n(Degraded)')
        axes[0, i].axis('off')
        
        axes[1, i].imshow(clean)
        axes[1, i].set_title('Clean')
        axes[1, i].axis('off')
    
    plt.suptitle('Cross-Domain Comparison: Degraded vs Clean', fontsize=14)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
else:
    print("  .")

imagenet-noise: 16371 samples
dibco: 9 samples
fmd: 3000 samples

def plot_histogram(image, title="", ax=None):
    """  """
    if ax is None:
        fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    
    if isinstance(image, torch.Tensor):
        image = image.numpy()
    
    colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue']
    for c, color in enumerate(colors):
        ax.hist(image[c].ravel(), bins=50, alpha=0.5, color=color, label=color.upper())
    
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.set_xlabel('Pixel Value')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()

if datasets:
    #     
    name, ds = list(datasets.items())[0]
    item = ds[0]
    
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))
    plot_histogram(item['degraded'], f'{name} - Degraded', axes[0])
    plot_histogram(item['clean'], f'{name} - Clean', axes[1])
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
